zlib is a compression library.

# Build HDF5
Check the version of OpenMPI. According to this (post)[https://forum.hdfgroup.org/t/hdf5-and-openmpi/5437], some failures have been observed when HDF5 is installed with certain versions of OpenMPI. I found that a particular test in `make check` (t_bigio) was hanging, so I made a local install of OpenMPI 4.0.0 and compiled HDF5 against this version instead, which seemed to solve the problem.

The `release_docs/INSTALL_parallel` file contains two sample programs in C and Fortran 90, respectively, which should be used to check the installation. Simply copy the programs into their own files (`Sample_mpio.c` and `Sample_mpio.f90`), compile, and run:
```bash
mpicc Sample_mpio.c -o c.out
mpiexec -np 4 c.out
mpif90 Sample_mpio.f90 -o f.out
mpiexec -np 4 c.out
```

